<section class="hero">
    <h1><em>Living</em> on Bitcoin</h1>
    <div class="hero-subtitle">Holding operating cash in bitcoin and paying fiat bills as they come due &mdash; a values-aligned practice with modest economics and real friction.</div>
    <p class="subtitle">For most bitcoiners, the case for bitcoin lives on the retirement page and the borrow-against-your-stack page &mdash; the surfaces where the asset's compounding actually does meaningful financial work. <em>Living on bitcoin</em> is something else: a day-to-day practice closer to identity than to yield, where the appreciation differential is real but small, the friction is real and recurring, and the psychological payoff is what most practitioners actually come for.</p>
</section>

